{"type":"text","timestamp":1782365810336,"sessionID":"ses_102b9de8dffe6FNc2AwM60MJ5O","part":{"id":"prt_efd47b3ef001hllSkfi9LfUc0f","messageID":"msg_efd4704630013YZsDoVs7ONPaB","sessionID":"ses_102b9de8dffe6FNc2AwM60MJ5O","type":"text","text":"I found the concrete parity gap: the current bootstrap shell always resets `isShellAtTop` to `true` on every route change, which weakens the source `LazyListState`/restore-state contract. I’m fixing that by introducing a small pure shell-route state helper in `app_router.cj`, updating the bootstrap page to use it, and extending phase-02 tests around tab reselection and preserved shell state.","time":{"start":1782365795311,"end":1782365810333}}}
