{"type":"text","timestamp":1782365994004,"sessionID":"ses_102b9de8dffe6FNc2AwM60MJ5O","part":{"id":"prt_efd4a8aab001AqGMsmYneGV5ze","messageID":"msg_efd4a7472001Zae6nK8tJfe0W0","sessionID":"ses_102b9de8dffe6FNc2AwM60MJ5O","type":"text","text":"Repaired the bounded group `phase-02-startup-navigation-session-source-behavior-presentation-util` by closing the two remaining critical `implemented-simplified` rows with a small target-side shell-state extraction, stronger tests, and updated matrix authority evidence.\n\n**Covered Current-Phase Gate Entries**\n- `app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-presentation-util-417c58decd-002-navigation-surface-menu-drawer-toolbar-o`\n  Status moved to `implemented` / `equivalent`.\n  The target now models shell commands explicitly via `ShellCommand` and `ShellRouteState`, and the bootstrap host uses that model directly for home/history tab commands, cart action, and primary action.\n- `app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-presentation-util-cb2f6fdad2-004-observable-state-viewmodel-flow-livedata`\n  Status moved to `implemented` / `equivalent`.\n  The target now preserves the combined route-plus-top-state shell visibility rule without resetting top-state on shell commands, which was the actual parity gap behind the previous simplification.\n\n**Remaining Current-Phase Gate Entries**\n- None in this implementation group after the two row updates.\n- I did not touch other phase-02 groups or broader planned rows outside this bounded repair.\n\n**Source Paths / Clusters Handled**\n- Source:\n  - `app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/util/Navigation.kt`\n  - `app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/util/Screen.kt`\n- Target:\n  - `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/app_router.cj`\n  - `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/bootstrap_page.cj`\n  - `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/test/cangjie/phase02_startup_navigation_test.cj`\n- Authority:\n  - `translation-inputs/source-coverage-matrix.json`\n  - `translation-inputs/source-coverage-matrix.md`\n\n**What Changed**\n- In `app_router.cj`\n  - Added `ShellCommand`.\n  - Added `ShellRouteState` with:\n    - `applyCommand`\n    - `setTopState`\n    - `showBottomShell`\n  - Kept route ids and shell gating in the same routing module, which makes the phase-02 shell contract precise and testable.\n- In `bootstrap_page.cj`\n  - Added `applyShellState`, `shellState`, and `applyShellCommand`.\n  - Switched bottom-shell buttons and primary action to use the shared shell-command model directly.\n  - Preserved manual route setting for non-shell destinations.\n  - Kept `currentRoute` and `isShellAtTop` as `@State`, but now route/top updates flow through one consistent helper.\n- In `phase02_startup_navigation_test.cj`\n  - Added `shellRouteStatePreservesTopFlagAcrossCommands`\n  - Added `shellRouteStatePrimaryActionUsesRouteContract`\n  - Existing shell-gating tests remain in place.\n\n**Why This Closed The Simplification Debt**\n- The previous target simplification was not just “no real feature pages yet”; it also encoded shell transitions as ad hoc page-state changes, which reset top-state too aggressively.\n- The source `Navigation.kt` contract depends on:\n  - route-aware shell visibility\n  - top-of-list awareness\n  - duplicate-safe tab behavior\n- The new `ShellRouteState` captures that contract directly in pure target code, and the bootstrap host now consumes it rather than bypassing it.\n\n**Tests Added Or Updated**\n- Updated:\n  - `entry/src/test/cangjie/phase02_startup_navigation_test.cj`\n- New coverage from tests:\n  - shell command behavior preserves top-state correctly\n  - primary action still follows the route contract\n  - bottom shell still only shows on top-level home/history\n\n**Commands Run**\n- `C:\\Users\\Sieger\\.cangjie-sdk\\6.1\\cangjie\\build-tools\\tools\\bin\\cjpm.exe test --target aarch64-linux-ohos`\n  - Run from `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\Foodike-Harmony\\entry`\n  - With the env overlay from the accepted phase-02 test report\n- `python.exe D:\\X2Cangjie\\X2Cangjie\\scripts\\shared\\source_coverage\\patch_authority.py --kind matrix ...`\n- `git status --short`\n\n**Build Result**\n- PASS for focused test reproduction:\n  - `cjpm test --target aarch64-linux-ohos`\n- The test run emitted warnings from ArkUI macro expansion and missing std dynamic library warning text, but ended with `cjpm test success`.\n\n**Out-Of-Scope Whole-Project Warnings**\n- The worktree contains many unrelated modified/untracked workflow and translation artifacts. I did not alter or normalize those.\n- There are still many planned rows across later phases and unassigned whole-project rows, but they are outside this bounded phase-02 group repair.\n\nChanged files:\n- `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/app_router.cj`: added explicit shell command/state model for duplicate-safe tab/cart/primary shell behavior.\n- `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/bootstrap_page.cj`: switched bootstrap host to use shared shell command/state helpers and preserve shell top-state across commands.\n- `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/test/cangjie/phase02_startup_navigation_test.cj`: added focused shell-state tests.\n- `translation-inputs/source-coverage-matrix.json`: promoted the two critical presentation/util rows from `implemented-simplified` to `implemented`.\n- `translation-inputs/source-coverage-matrix.md`: synced markdown mirror after authority patch.\n- `translation-inputs/agent-inputs/phase02_presentation_util_patch.json`: temporary strict patch payload used for the authority update.\n\nCommands run:\n- `C:\\Users\\Sieger\\.cangjie-sdk\\6.1\\cangjie\\build-tools\\tools\\bin\\cjpm.exe test --target aarch64-linux-ohos`\n- `C:\\Users\\Sieger\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Python\\Python312\\python.exe D:\\X2Cangjie\\X2Cangjie\\scripts\\shared\\source_coverage\\patch_authority.py --kind matrix --authority D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\source-coverage-matrix.json --patch D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\agent-inputs\\phase02_presentation_util_patch.json --markdown D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\source-coverage-matrix.md --plan-json D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\plan.json --target-project D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\Foodike-Harmony`\n- `git status --short`\n\nBuild result:\n- PASS: focused test reproduction succeeded for phase-02 shell behavior.\n\nPlan changes:\n- none\n\nDeferred issues:\n- none for this bounded group\n\nNext recommended action:\n- Let the runner refresh `phase-group-verdicts`; this group should now recompute as complete.","time":{"start":1782365981355,"end":1782365994002}}}
